kernel-image-di (0.011) unstable; urgency=low

  * Rebuilt with kernel-source-2.4.2 2.4.2-3, to get initrd freeing fix,
    and initrd on cramfs support.
  * Also turned on tmpfs, for playing with as a better ramfs than ramfs.
  * Turned OFF cramfs, after noticing this:
      831k    cramfs-mnt/var/lib/dpkg/info
      110k    ext2-mnt/var/lib/dpkg/info
    Same contents; cramfs does poorly with lots of small files, compared to
    appropriatly tuned ext2.
  * Well, I'll leave cramfs as a module.

 -- Joey Hess <joeyh@debian.org>  Sun, 25 Mar 2001 18:44:27 -0800

kernel-image-di (0.010) unstable; urgency=low

  * Updated to 2.4.2 kernel.
  * Fixed Binary: line in .dsc file. This was painful, and involded adding
    a control.template to the package, which is what should be edited form
    now on. debian/control is automatically generated, but I am leaving it
    in cvs so one can check out the package and build it with
    dpkg-buildpackage.
  * Made kernel image deb depend on initrd-tools.

 -- Joey Hess <joeyh@debian.org>  Fri,  9 Mar 2001 11:48:40 -0800

