kernel-image-di (0.004) unstable; urgency=low

  * Added another udeb that holds the actual kernel image. This is
    handy because the d-i build system can then just install that udeb and
    move the kernel image onto the boot floppy image. And the udeb will
    be listed in d-i's status file, so all the module dependancies will
    be met.
  * Correct override disparities, I hope.

 -- Joey Hess <joeyh@debian.org>  Wed, 31 Jan 2001 21:03:35 -0800

